Page 230.<br/>Environmental changes might lead to a conflict and possibly to an international war as a result of
 1) <strong>Food shortages</strong> due to decreases in net global agricultural production;
 2) <strong>Decreased availability and quality of fresh water</strong> in key regions due to shifted precipitation patterns, causing more frequent floods and droughts;
 3) <strong>Disrupted access to energy supplies</strong> due to extensive sea ice and storminess.
